st:2: good friday
r: On this day the ministers enter in silence.
r: All then kneel for silent prayer.
r: The Officiant rises and may say
v: All we like sheep have gone astray;
v: we have turned every one to his own way,
v:people: And the Lord has laid on him the iniquity of us all.

r: The Officiant says
v: Let us pray.

tb: Almighty God, we beseech you graciously to behold this your
    family, for whom our Lord Jesus Christ was willing to be
    betrayed and given into the hands of sinners, and to suffer death
    upon the Cross; who now lives and reigns with you and the
    Holy Spirit, one God, for ever and ever. **Amen.**

st: the lessons
l: {{u}}genesis{{\u}} 22:1-18 _or_ {{u}}isaiah{{\u}} 52:13—53:12
l: {{u}}psalm{{\u}} 22:1-11 (12-21) v _or_ 40:1-16 v _or_ 69:1-22 v
